---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | Qibla Now" description="Qibla Now is designed as a focused religious utility that respects user privacy. This application does not require accounts, does not collect personal profiles, and does not operate a backend service for core functionality.">
  <section class="section">
    <h1>Privacy Policy for Qibla Now</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> 2026-01-01<br />
    <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://qibla-now.com">https://qibla-now.com</a><br />
    <strong>Application:</strong> Qibla Now (Android)</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>Qibla Now is designed as a focused religious utility that respects user privacy. This application does not require accounts, does not collect personal profiles, and does not operate a backend service for core functionality.</p>
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains what data the app may access, how it is used, and what external services may be involved.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
    <p>Qibla Now <strong>does not collect or store personal data on its own servers</strong>.</p>
    <p>The application operates primarily <strong>offline</strong> and performs calculations directly on the device.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Names</li>
      <li>Email addresses</li>
      <li>Location history</li>
      <li>Device identifiers</li>
      <li>Usage analytics</li>
      <li>Behavioral tracking data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>No user account or registration is required to use the application.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>2. Location Information</h2>
    <p>The application may request access to the device's <strong>precise location</strong> in order to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Calculate prayer times</li>
      <li>Determine the direction of the Qibla</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Location data is used <strong>only locally on the device</strong> for these calculations and is <strong>not transmitted to the developer or stored remotely</strong>.</p>
    <p>Users may alternatively choose to manually set a location instead of granting location access.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>3. Notifications</h2>
    <p>If enabled by the user, the application schedules <strong>local notifications</strong> on the device to alert for prayer times.</p>
    <p>These notifications are generated and managed entirely on the device. No remote notification service is used by the application.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>4. Internet Access</h2>
    <p>Most features of Qibla Now work without an internet connection.</p>
    <p>Internet access may be used for optional features such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Loading map tiles when viewing the map screen</li>
      <li>Displaying advertisements if ads are enabled in the application</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These external services may process network requests according to their own privacy policies.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>5. Advertising</h2>
    <p>Qibla Now may display <strong>non-personalized advertisements</strong>.</p>
    <p>Ads are limited to banner formats and are configured to avoid behavioral profiling.</p>
    <p>Advertising services may collect limited technical information required to display ads, such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Device type</li>
      <li>Approximate location derived from IP address</li>
      <li>Advertising identifiers provided by the operating system</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These services operate under their own privacy policies.</p>
    <p>Users can reset or limit advertising identifiers in their device settings.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>6. Data Storage</h2>
    <p>All user preferences and configuration settings are stored <strong>locally on the device</strong>.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Selected prayer calculation method</li>
      <li>Madhab preference</li>
      <li>Location settings</li>
      <li>Notification configuration</li>
      <li>Display preferences</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This information is not transmitted to the developer.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Qibla Now does not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>
    <p>Because the application does not collect personal data or require accounts, it is suitable for general audiences.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>The application may interact with third-party services such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Map providers</li>
      <li>Advertising networks</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These services may process network requests independently and are governed by their own privacy policies.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>Since Qibla Now does not operate a backend service and stores data locally on the device, the risk of remote data exposure is minimized.</p>
    <p>Users are responsible for maintaining the security of their device.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy may be updated in future versions of the application.</p>
    <p>Updates will be published on the official website:</p>
    <p><a href="https://qibla-now.com/privacy">https://qibla-now.com/privacy</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Developer:</strong> Juan G. Carmona</li>
      <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://qibla-now.com">https://qibla-now.com</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>